Colombian President Back Home From Peruvian Visit 
Colombian President Andres Pastrana left here Tuesday for home after
ending a three-day official visit to Peru.
During the visit, Pastrana met with his Peruvian counterpart Valentin
Paniagua and the two leaders pledged to commit themselves to forging an
Andean Strategy Against Drug-Trafficking as soon as possible.
They also signed a protocol on modifying the Reciprocal Investment
Protection and Promotion Agreement and a joint declaration.
During his stay, Pastrana discussed with leaders of two major Peruvian
parties regional issues such as the fight against drug-trafficking,
terrorism and corruption, as well as border development projects and
the potential of the Andean Community and the Free Trade Area of the
Americas (AFTA).
